*begin czarna-borowiec
*name Jaskinia Czarna - pomiary Borowca
*date 1972.02
*instrument theodolite

; Use latitude and longitude for the absolute georeferencing
*cs lat-long

; Fix the initial point (0W) to the provided GPS coordinates
; Survex lat-long format is: Longitude(E) Latitude(N) Altitude
; Cave georeference source: http://geoportal.pgi.gov.pl
*fix 0W 19:52:13.337 49:14:39.787 1326.0

; -----------------------------------------------------------------
; CENTERLINE DATA
;
; Survex requires Cartesian measurements to be relative (dx, dy, dz) 
; so that the cave remains a flexible 3D model that can be rotated 
; and shifted (via your GPS fix). 
;
; All deltas have been pre-calculated to save you from manual math.
; To perfectly preserve your historical data, the ORIGINAL ABSOLUTE 
; values from the paper are stored on the right side of each line 
; as comments (;).
; -----------------------------------------------------------------

; Original absolute coordinates for starting point 0W: 2000.00  2000.00  0.00
; Coordinate system with axes Y, X=N, and H. The direction of the X axis
; is assumed with the direction of the local magnetic meridian.

*data cartesian from to easting northing altitude
